               <p>WILLIAM CLAPP. I live with my father, in <placeName id="t18301209-187-crimeloc1052">Kingsland-road</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18301209-187-crimeloc1052" type="placeName" value="Kingsland-road"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18301209-187-crimeloc1052" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18301209-187-off1050 t18301209-187-crimeloc1052"></join>. On the evening of the 30th of November I was at my father's door, and saw the prisoner; he passed and looked very hard at me - I watched him, and saw him cross to Mr. Champion's door; he unpinned these stockings, which were hanging at the door - I called my father's apprentice, who ran after him; I saw the prisoner fold up the stockings and put them under his coat.</p>

               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18301209-187-person1653">
                  JOHN 
                  WARLEY
               <interp inst="t18301209-187-person1653" type="surname" value="WARLEY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18301209-187-person1653" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18301209-187-person1653" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am the officer. My wife told me the prosecutor had been robbed of some stockings - the prisoner had then got into his own house; one of the boys knocked at the door, and when I got in I found these stockings under the bed, and no one but the prisoner was in the room.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18301209-187-person1654">
                  HENRY 
                  ROWLAND
               <interp inst="t18301209-187-person1654" type="surname" value="ROWLAND"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18301209-187-person1654" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18301209-187-person1654" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I went after the prisoner - he looked at me, gave a sudden turn, and went through a public-house.</p>
               <p>WILLIAM CHAMPION. I am the <rs id="t18301209-187-viclabel1053" type="occupation">owner of the shop</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18301209-187-victim1652 t18301209-187-viclabel1053"></join>. These are my stockings - I missed two like them, but it is impossible to swear to a stocking.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. They took one boy first, and then came and took me.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18301209-187-verdict1054" type="verdictDescription">
